{"title":"E. Tetrahedron","contestId":"166","problemIndex":"E","timeLimit":"2 seconds","memLimit":"256 megabytes","inputFormat":"standard input","outputFormat":"standard output","problemHtml":"<p>You are given a tetrahedron. Let&apos;s mark its vertices with letters <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>A</i></span>, <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>B</i></span>, <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>C</i></span> and <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>D</i></span> correspondingly.</p><p></p><center> <img class=\"tex-graphics\" src=\"https://espresso.codeforces.com/4ef1e5eb6931a35fcb7616bf8cf6a20b2ff1f6c6.png\" style=\"max-width: 100.0%;max-height: 100.0%;\"> </center><p></p><p>An ant is standing in the vertex <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>D</i></span> of the tetrahedron. The ant is quite active and he wouldn&apos;t stay idle. At each moment of time he makes a step from one vertex to another one along some edge of the tetrahedron. The ant just can&apos;t stand on one place.</p><p>You do not have to do much to solve the problem: your task is to count the number of ways in which the ant can go from the initial vertex <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>D</i></span> to itself in exactly <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>n</i></span> steps. In other words, you are asked to find out the number of different cyclic paths with the length of <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>n</i></span> from vertex <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>D</i></span> to itself. As the number can be quite large, you should print it modulo <span class=\"tex-span\">1000000007</span> (<span class=\"tex-span\">10<sup class=\"upper-index\">9</sup>&#x2009;+&#x2009;7</span>). </p>","inSpecsHtml":"<div class=\"section-title\">Input</div><p>The first line contains the only integer <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>n</i></span> (<span class=\"tex-span\">1&#x2009;&#x2264;&#x2009;<i>n</i>&#x2009;&#x2264;&#x2009;10<sup class=\"upper-index\">7</sup></span>) &#x2014; the required length of the cyclic path.</p>","outSpecsHtml":"<div class=\"section-title\">Output</div><p>Print the only integer &#x2014; the required number of ways modulo <span class=\"tex-span\">1000000007</span> (<span class=\"tex-span\">10<sup class=\"upper-index\">9</sup>&#x2009;+&#x2009;7</span>).</p>","noteHtml":"<div class=\"section-title\">Note</div><p>The required paths in the first sample are: </p><ul> <li> <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>D</i>&#x2009;-&#x2009;<i>A</i>&#x2009;-&#x2009;<i>D</i></span> </li><li> <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>D</i>&#x2009;-&#x2009;<i>B</i>&#x2009;-&#x2009;<i>D</i></span> </li><li> <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>D</i>&#x2009;-&#x2009;<i>C</i>&#x2009;-&#x2009;<i>D</i></span> </li></ul><p></p>","sampleTestcases":[{"id":1613164623780,"input":"2\n","output":"3\n"},{"id":1613164623781,"input":"4\n","output":"21\n"}],"submitUrl":"https://codeforces.com/problemset/submit","language":"c++"}